HTTPS Interception
Burp decrypts HTTPS traffic using its own trusted Certificate Authority (CA) certificate.

The built-in Chromium browser already trusts Burp's certificate, making HTTPS interception work without additional configuration.

Pentester's Perspective 🔍
For every intercepted request, ask:

Can I modify parameters?
Can I change HTTP methods?
Can I change cookies?
Can I modify JWTs?
Can I access hidden endpoints?
Can I change request headers?
Interview Questions
What is Burp Proxy?
Burp Proxy intercepts HTTP/HTTPS traffic between the browser and the server.

What is Repeater?
Repeater allows testers to resend modified requests multiple times without using the browser.

Why use Repeater?
To manually test application behavior by changing requests and observing responses.

